1
00:00:23,451 --> 00:00:26,218
Here, we teach all our students

2
00:00:28,340 --> 00:00:30,000
To be well-behaved

3
00:00:33,349 --> 00:00:34,777
Compassionate.

4
00:00:35,317 --> 00:00:37,211
I told you to bow down!

5
00:00:39,363 --> 00:00:40,556
Honest.

6
00:00:44,024 --> 00:00:45,921
And morally righteous.

7
00:00:50,144 --> 00:00:51,930
And they can't just be white.

8
00:00:54,002 --> 00:00:57,082
They must be flawlessly pure.

9
00:01:04,506 --> 00:01:06,695
I am very pleased and glad

10
00:01:07,195 --> 00:01:09,560
that an idealistic alumna like you

11
00:01:10,240 --> 00:01:13,491
is interested in returning here as a teacher.

12
00:01:15,121 --> 00:01:17,258
I believe that a good role model

13
00:01:17,259 --> 00:01:21,064
will naturally mold pure white students.

14
00:01:24,782 --> 00:01:26,317
But I'm quite surprised.

15
00:01:26,857 --> 00:01:30,490
What made you choose to come back to our school?

16
00:01:35,160 --> 00:01:37,123
As you may know, Mother Superior.

17
00:01:41,162 --> 00:01:44,555
My mom and I have been alone since I was little.

18
00:01:46,747 --> 00:01:48,760
When I went to study abroad,

19
00:01:49,267 --> 00:01:51,084
she had to live all by herself.

20
00:01:52,759 --> 00:01:56,165
When I was coming back, she was so happy.

21
00:01:56,166 --> 00:01:59,475
She planned to surprise me at the airport.

22
00:02:07,325 --> 00:02:08,985
But on the day I arrived,

23
00:02:09,411 --> 00:02:10,745
she wasn't there.

24
00:02:20,815 --> 00:02:22,268
Because she couldn't make it.

25
00:02:29,840 --> 00:02:31,201
The doctor said

26
00:02:33,282 --> 00:02:36,048
she has advanced colon cancer.

27
00:02:43,775 --> 00:02:45,288
The reason I decided

28
00:02:46,352 --> 00:02:49,571
to apply for the French teacher position here

29
00:02:49,572 --> 00:02:52,430
is because this school is near her house

30
00:02:52,710 --> 00:02:54,350
and the hospital.

31
00:02:58,855 --> 00:03:00,607
I want to spend time with her

32
00:03:02,147 --> 00:03:04,293
as much as I possibly can.

33
00:03:09,265 --> 00:03:10,625
I am so sorry to hear that.

34
00:03:11,555 --> 00:03:14,767
Please send my regards to Teacher Niramon too.

35
00:03:19,007 --> 00:03:23,900
I'm planning to raise the standard of our language arts students,

36
00:03:24,720 --> 00:03:29,206
so they can win academic awards like the science students.

37
00:03:31,690 --> 00:03:34,056
But that requires a lot of time

38
00:03:34,575 --> 00:03:37,750
and extra dedication to the students.

39
00:03:37,751 --> 00:03:39,950
After hearing about your mother,

40
00:03:41,727 --> 00:03:43,247
I'm just not sure

41
00:03:43,640 --> 00:03:46,390
if this job is right for you.

42
00:03:49,260 --> 00:03:51,230
If it's about tutoring kids for competitions,

43
00:03:53,541 --> 00:03:56,280
I'm completely confident that I can do it.

44
00:03:56,281 --> 00:03:57,799
Because I normally

45
00:03:57,800 --> 00:04:00,533
teach French as a tutor anyway. As for...

46
00:04:00,534 --> 00:04:03,686
But teaching students who want to learn is easy.

47
00:04:03,687 --> 00:04:06,836
Dealing with kids who have no goals, however...

48
00:04:07,206 --> 00:04:09,056
that's a whole different ball game.

49
00:04:10,787 --> 00:04:12,590
But your advantage, Nalin,

50
00:04:13,010 --> 00:04:15,574
is that you're not much older than our students.

51
00:04:16,267 --> 00:04:20,110
Getting them to open up to you shouldn't be a problem.

52
00:04:22,072 --> 00:04:25,070
I'm willing to hire you right now

53
00:04:26,478 --> 00:04:29,650
if you can promise me one thing.

54
00:04:38,274 --> 00:04:39,660
What is it?

55
00:05:34,188 --> 00:05:35,188
Oops!

56
00:05:36,536 --> 00:05:37,924
I'm sorry.

57
00:05:38,185 --> 00:05:40,525
Welcome, new student.

58
00:05:43,588 --> 00:05:44,808
Do it like this.

59
00:05:45,356 --> 00:05:48,128
Put your hands together like this.

60
00:05:48,129 --> 00:05:49,635
And bend your knees.

61
00:05:50,593 --> 00:05:51,625
Bend down.

62
00:05:52,292 --> 00:05:53,531
Lower.

63
00:05:53,745 --> 00:05:54,932
A bit lower.

64
00:05:57,338 --> 00:06:01,168
Our school has a unique way of doing the wai.

65
00:06:01,585 --> 00:06:04,154
Practice a bit more and you'll get used to it.

66
00:06:04,904 --> 00:06:06,560
Let me see you try.

67
00:06:08,263 --> 00:06:09,857
Try to wai again.

68
00:06:14,702 --> 00:06:16,015
Very good.

69
00:06:16,352 --> 00:06:17,395
Hello, Mother.

70
00:06:17,396 --> 00:06:18,587
Hello.

71
00:06:20,346 --> 00:06:24,319
If you're ready, let me show you around the school.

72
00:06:24,320 --> 00:06:25,343
Yes, let's go.

73
00:06:30,079 --> 00:06:35,560
This entire area is where parents can wait for their children.

74
00:06:35,561 --> 00:06:38,241
But the school doesn't allow parents

75
00:06:38,242 --> 00:06:42,113
to go into the inner zones where the students are.

76
00:06:58,578 --> 00:07:00,382
This is Teacher Nalin.

77
00:07:00,942 --> 00:07:05,786
How lucky that Suchada's homeroom teacher is here today.

78
00:07:06,570 --> 00:07:08,496
I'll take this opportunity

79
00:07:08,497 --> 00:07:12,336
for the teacher and the new student to get to know each other.

80
00:07:13,195 --> 00:07:15,123
As for the parents,

81
00:07:15,124 --> 00:07:17,243
please proceed to the finance room.

82
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:19,933
If it's about money,

83
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:22,084
I can go alone.

84
00:07:22,590 --> 00:07:24,840
Oh, certainly. Please go ahead.

85
00:07:37,222 --> 00:07:38,782
Is this size okay?

86
00:07:40,350 --> 00:07:43,505
Actually, students here usually wear it a bit shorter.

87
00:07:44,708 --> 00:07:46,162
Are you afraid it'll look awkward?

88
00:07:48,591 --> 00:07:50,805
But I think it's better to stick to the rules for now.

89
00:07:51,462 --> 00:07:53,729
Oh... Not "I".

90
00:07:55,208 --> 00:07:57,667
Teacher thinks it's better to stick to the rules for now.

91
00:07:59,748 --> 00:08:01,675
Did you just move here too?

92
00:08:02,921 --> 00:08:03,961
Yeah.

93
00:08:05,301 --> 00:08:08,499
I'm actually an alumna here.

94
00:08:09,766 --> 00:08:11,296
Just started as a teacher.

95
00:08:13,787 --> 00:08:15,314
What about you?

96
00:08:15,751 --> 00:08:17,717
Why did you transfer in the middle of the year?

97
00:08:20,840 --> 00:08:24,408
I had to move houses suddenly.

98
00:08:38,089 --> 00:08:39,854
Nice to meet you.

99
00:08:43,949 --> 00:08:47,990
I'll consider you my first friend here.

100
00:08:52,141 --> 00:08:54,228
If you need any advice,

101
00:08:54,762 --> 00:08:56,335
just tell me.

102
00:08:57,880 --> 00:09:02,674
You can talk to me as a teacher or as a senior.

103
00:09:05,662 --> 00:09:07,216
So...

104
00:09:08,030 --> 00:09:10,668
Teacher Nalin, have you ever broken the school rules?

105
00:09:15,042 --> 00:09:17,516
Someone might see us.

106
00:09:18,070 --> 00:09:20,816
It's the weekend, no one's around to see.

107
00:09:54,245 --> 00:09:55,700
Not really.

108
00:10:01,010 --> 00:10:02,230
So...

109
00:10:02,390 --> 00:10:05,970
As a senior, do you have any advice for me?

110
00:10:07,152 --> 00:10:08,638
Hmm...

111
00:10:08,807 --> 00:10:10,605
Actually, an all-girls school

112
00:10:10,606 --> 00:10:12,700
isn't that different from a regular school.

113
00:10:14,847 --> 00:10:17,578
It's just that there can be some issues

114
00:10:17,579 --> 00:10:19,911
when a lot of girls get together.

115
00:10:20,748 --> 00:10:23,243
They tend to just follow what others are doing.

116
00:10:23,656 --> 00:10:25,223
Especially if there's a conflict,

117
00:10:25,560 --> 00:10:28,766
they might take their friends' sides regardless of who's right or wrong.

118
00:10:33,571 --> 00:10:36,528
If you ever find yourself in a difficult situation,

119
00:10:38,827 --> 00:10:40,534
my advice would be

120
00:10:40,795 --> 00:10:43,535
to trust your instincts

121
00:10:45,841 --> 00:10:47,607
and do what's right.

122
00:10:48,947 --> 00:10:53,026
Then life will attract the right kind of people to be your friends.

123
00:10:56,015 --> 00:10:59,076
Oh wow, I was just asking playfully,

124
00:10:59,077 --> 00:11:01,170
but I got a really serious answer!

125
00:11:03,374 --> 00:11:06,386
But thank you, Teacher Nalin.

126
00:11:07,970 --> 00:11:10,193
I'll go get your textbooks for you.

127
00:11:29,112 --> 00:11:30,064
It's gone.

128
00:11:30,065 --> 00:11:31,727
How much did you borrow from them?

129
00:11:32,814 --> 00:11:35,195
Why are you acting like this?

130
00:11:35,196 --> 00:11:36,921
And where is the money now?

131
00:11:36,922 --> 00:11:38,707
Why would you do this?

132
00:11:39,129 --> 00:11:40,380
Huh?

133
00:11:40,381 --> 00:11:43,495
I invested it with a friend, but they ran off.

134
00:11:44,341 --> 00:11:47,122
Are you hiding anything else from me?

135
00:11:47,616 --> 00:11:48,490
And...

136
00:11:49,423 --> 00:11:51,455
Don't you even think about Jane?

137
00:11:51,456 --> 00:11:53,619
If she had come home early today,

138
00:11:54,300 --> 00:11:55,827
what could have happened?

139
00:11:55,828 --> 00:11:58,190
Why couldn't you think about that?

140
00:11:58,191 --> 00:11:59,877
Calm down.

141
00:11:59,877 --> 00:12:01,867
Don't you get involved, Pim!

142
00:12:01,867 --> 00:12:03,127
Just listen to me.

143
00:12:15,057 --> 00:12:16,226
Jane.

144
00:12:20,496 --> 00:12:21,978
When the new semester starts,

145
00:12:22,523 --> 00:12:25,002
you'll have to go live with your dad in Bangkok for a while.

146
00:12:28,522 --> 00:12:31,069
You wanted to go to college in Bangkok anyway, right?

147
00:12:32,612 --> 00:12:35,140
Going a year early shouldn't be a big deal, right?

148
00:12:38,443 --> 00:12:40,263
Can't I go later, Mom?

149
00:12:40,863 --> 00:12:43,090
Let me at least finish 11th grade here.

150
00:12:47,396 --> 00:12:49,037
Your dad asked for this.

151
00:12:50,390 --> 00:12:51,532
But...

152
00:12:52,010 --> 00:12:55,702
I already told him you want to study art, and...

153
00:12:56,473 --> 00:12:59,890
if you need money for art tutoring,

154
00:13:02,728 --> 00:13:05,116
he can definitely support you better than I can.

155
00:13:20,210 --> 00:13:23,173
Once everything settles down,

156
00:13:24,950 --> 00:13:27,272
I'll come get you so we can be together again.

157
00:13:50,624 --> 00:13:52,507
The seller told me

158
00:13:53,744 --> 00:13:56,319
that if a mother sharpens a pencil for her child...

159
00:13:57,012 --> 00:13:59,780
the drawings will turn out extra beautiful.

160
00:14:05,729 --> 00:14:07,040
Stay strong, honey.

161
00:14:14,161 --> 00:14:16,789
Can you call me often, Mom?

162
00:14:23,923 --> 00:14:25,667
Why are you even asking?

163
00:14:27,488 --> 00:14:29,552
Of course I have to call you.

164
00:14:29,553 --> 00:14:30,758
Please, Mom.

165
00:14:31,055 --> 00:14:32,915
Call me often, okay?

166
00:14:54,306 --> 00:14:56,147
Be a good girl, okay?

167
00:14:56,809 --> 00:14:59,802
Don't stay out late, and don't be stubborn with your dad.

168
00:15:01,702 --> 00:15:03,268
And I'll be back soon.

169
00:15:30,817 --> 00:15:32,197
Hi, Dad.

170
00:15:32,198 --> 00:15:33,356
Hey, Jane.

171
00:15:33,770 --> 00:15:35,056
Come here for a second.

172
00:15:35,057 --> 00:15:36,550
I have something for you.

173
00:15:39,237 --> 00:15:40,224
Here.

174
00:15:40,344 --> 00:15:42,227
Your mom told me

175
00:15:43,282 --> 00:15:45,042
that you like drawing.

176
00:15:46,606 --> 00:15:48,406
So, I bought this for you.

177
00:15:56,778 --> 00:15:58,038
From now on,

178
00:15:58,039 --> 00:16:00,393
if you want anything, just let me know.

179
00:16:00,965 --> 00:16:02,953
I'm ready to fully support you.

180
00:16:09,557 --> 00:16:10,950
Open it up and see.

181
00:16:11,625 --> 00:16:13,052
It's the newest model.

182
00:16:13,589 --> 00:16:15,049
Thanks, Dad.

183
00:17:14,811 --> 00:17:15,855
Oops.

184
00:17:16,926 --> 00:17:19,159
Sorry, I didn't mean to.

185
00:17:19,907 --> 00:17:21,466
That's okay.

186
00:17:52,421 --> 00:17:54,780
Hey, what's up?

187
00:17:55,279 --> 00:17:57,166
Long time no see.

188
00:17:57,654 --> 00:17:59,188
I missed you.

189
00:18:04,612 --> 00:18:06,206
It's still morning.

190
00:18:06,447 --> 00:18:08,521
We've done it earlier than this, haven't we?

191
00:18:21,485 --> 00:18:23,195
See you later.

192
00:18:23,196 --> 00:18:25,023
I really have to go.

193
00:18:38,875 --> 00:18:41,561
Hi, P'Amy.

194
00:18:41,562 --> 00:18:43,262
Hi there.

195
00:19:05,912 --> 00:19:07,274
How are you feeling?

196
00:19:15,753 --> 00:19:17,127
You feel hot.

197
00:19:17,393 --> 00:19:21,312
I bought a flu test kit and some medicine.

198
00:19:22,334 --> 00:19:23,721
No need to test.

199
00:19:24,764 --> 00:19:26,498
I caught it from you anyway.

200
00:19:28,401 --> 00:19:30,774
I told you we should sleep in separate rooms.

201
00:19:31,313 --> 00:19:32,740
But you didn't listen.

202
00:19:33,744 --> 00:19:35,499
I went to your house...

203
00:19:36,072 --> 00:19:38,014
to sleep with you, you know.

204
00:19:39,335 --> 00:19:41,743
If we had slept in separate rooms...

205
00:19:43,065 --> 00:19:44,612
what a waste that would be.

206
00:19:55,813 --> 00:19:58,665
It's just the first day of school, and someone couldn't resist.

207
00:19:59,165 --> 00:20:01,485
Leaving a lipstick mark on P'Amy this early in the morning?

208
00:20:17,619 --> 00:20:19,039
You'll get infected.

209
00:20:20,198 --> 00:20:21,465
I won't.

210
00:20:22,012 --> 00:20:23,620
I'm immune now.

211
00:21:16,644 --> 00:21:17,825
What the hell?

212
00:21:24,174 --> 00:21:25,701
She's a girl,

213
00:21:25,702 --> 00:21:28,889
but her parents just let her ride a motorcycle to school.

214
00:21:35,978 --> 00:21:37,210
I've transferred it.

215
00:21:37,490 --> 00:21:39,475
Hey, wait, kid.

216
00:21:39,476 --> 00:21:41,541
Did you transfer too much? It's a whole thousand.

217
00:21:41,542 --> 00:21:44,284
Oh, that's for the paint scratch.

218
00:21:44,285 --> 00:21:45,824
She's my friend.

219
00:21:52,872 --> 00:21:54,066
Oops!

220
00:21:54,300 --> 00:21:56,693
Whoa, you scared me!

221
00:21:56,694 --> 00:21:58,481
What are you playing at?

222
00:22:05,782 --> 00:22:07,718
We're almost at school.

223
00:22:08,650 --> 00:22:09,950
So what?

224
00:22:10,909 --> 00:22:12,143
Let's go eat on that side.

225
00:22:12,144 --> 00:22:14,965
No, we're already late.

226
00:22:19,171 --> 00:22:22,918
Oh, so on the first day of school, you're rushing to serve Nano?

227
00:22:22,919 --> 00:22:25,484
I'm just going to save a seat for my friend.

228
00:22:26,019 --> 00:22:27,701
That's serving.

229
00:22:28,248 --> 00:22:31,042
Someone with no friends like you wouldn't understand.

230
00:22:31,043 --> 00:22:33,499
Well, want to try?

231
00:22:34,055 --> 00:22:36,274
Having no friends means you don't have to care about anyone.

232
00:22:36,793 --> 00:22:38,389
It's quite relaxing.

233
00:22:43,808 --> 00:22:47,173
Wow, so mean. I haven't even eaten yet.

234
00:23:07,480 --> 00:23:08,773
Hello.

235
00:23:08,861 --> 00:23:10,726
Earn, did you save the seats?

236
00:23:10,727 --> 00:23:13,308
I'm sorry, I just got to school.

237
00:23:13,309 --> 00:23:15,673
Ugh, why didn't you tell me earlier?

238
00:23:15,674 --> 00:23:17,321
I told you we're sitting in the same spot!

239
00:23:20,161 --> 00:23:21,758
Getting yelled at bright and early again, huh?

240
00:23:24,358 --> 00:23:25,215
Look,

241
00:23:25,641 --> 00:23:27,638
I'm not trying to rub it in or anything.

242
00:23:28,600 --> 00:23:31,666
Why do you put up with people who just use you to do things for them?

243
00:23:31,963 --> 00:23:34,612
At least no one bullies me like they used to.

244
00:23:43,309 --> 00:23:45,462
Is Earn just innocent, or is she stupid?

245
00:23:45,463 --> 00:23:47,415
She's late and didn't even say anything.

246
00:23:49,721 --> 00:23:51,631
Where are we gonna sit now?

247
00:23:51,632 --> 00:23:53,647
If I knew, I would have had you save the seats in the first place

248
00:23:53,648 --> 00:23:55,154
so we didn't have to wait for Earn.

249
00:23:55,155 --> 00:23:57,801
It's always like this. All talk and no action.

250
00:23:58,191 --> 00:23:59,833
So irresponsible.

251
00:24:16,537 --> 00:24:18,037
I want to sit in our usual spot.

252
00:24:19,832 --> 00:24:22,247
Who is that? A new kid?

253
00:24:24,966 --> 00:24:26,280
Let's go sit in our usual spot.

254
00:24:45,162 --> 00:24:46,168
Get up.

255
00:24:52,404 --> 00:24:53,518
Get up.

256
00:24:54,787 --> 00:24:56,265
Why should I get up?

257
00:24:59,579 --> 00:25:02,814
The seats by the window belong to our group.

258
00:25:03,249 --> 00:25:06,409
If you want to sit here, you have to join our group.

259
00:25:06,410 --> 00:25:07,902
Are you interested?

260
00:25:10,494 --> 00:25:11,627
Sure.

261
00:25:11,931 --> 00:25:14,906
I'm Jane, I just moved here from Chiang Rai.

262
00:25:17,090 --> 00:25:18,952
The mole on your nose is pretty.

263
00:25:21,020 --> 00:25:22,273
What's so funny?

264
00:25:33,211 --> 00:25:34,977
Hey, what are you doing?

265
00:25:43,322 --> 00:25:45,035
Students, pay respect.

266
00:25:46,630 --> 00:25:48,790
Hello.

267
00:25:52,963 --> 00:25:54,982
Hello, everyone.

268
00:25:55,382 --> 00:25:57,846
Welcome to the new semester.

269
00:25:58,245 --> 00:26:02,260
I hope students in Grade 11C will study hard

270
00:26:02,261 --> 00:26:05,299
and be a good example for the 10th graders.

271
00:26:10,878 --> 00:26:12,706
Nice to meet all of you.

272
00:26:12,999 --> 00:26:14,170
I'm Teacher Nalin.

273
00:26:15,803 --> 00:26:18,660
I'll be the homeroom teacher for Grade 11C,

274
00:26:18,661 --> 00:26:20,988
the French Arts track, this semester.

275
00:26:22,176 --> 00:26:24,471
And I will also be teaching you all French.

276
00:26:24,805 --> 00:26:26,318
What about Teacher Som?

277
00:26:28,795 --> 00:26:32,090
Teacher Som got fired, right? So you got to replace her.

278
00:26:32,263 --> 00:26:34,194
Regarding Teacher Thanida,

279
00:26:34,487 --> 00:26:37,371
it was her own decision to resign.

280
00:26:39,012 --> 00:26:40,038
Really?

281
00:26:41,202 --> 00:26:44,662
You didn't force her out

282
00:26:44,663 --> 00:26:46,856
because you thought she was making sex content?

283
00:26:51,799 --> 00:26:53,841
Her face wasn't even in the content.

284
00:26:54,207 --> 00:26:57,964
Could you really tell it was Teacher Som just by seeing her naked?

285
00:26:58,864 --> 00:27:02,419
You're so sure, as if you're a monthly subscriber, Mother.

286
00:27:02,739 --> 00:27:06,377
No one asked for your opinion, Nicharee.

287
00:27:08,474 --> 00:27:12,209
To ensure no one displays arrogant behavior like yours again,

288
00:27:12,210 --> 00:27:15,179
I'll be deducting behavior points from all of you.

289
00:27:16,174 --> 00:27:17,634
5 points each.

290
00:27:19,438 --> 00:27:23,750
Don't forget that here, we are collectively responsible.

291
00:28:04,697 --> 00:28:06,404
The social security she's been using

292
00:28:06,405 --> 00:28:08,893
might not cover this specific drug.

293
00:28:09,341 --> 00:28:12,688
And the patient has already gone through the hardest part.

294
00:28:12,689 --> 00:28:15,446
If you can afford it, I'd suggest fighting on.

295
00:28:17,924 --> 00:28:20,183
And when should my mom start taking the medicine?

296
00:28:20,676 --> 00:28:24,549
The sooner the better for her.

297
00:28:27,324 --> 00:28:29,273
Anyway, excuse me for now.

298
00:28:39,268 --> 00:28:42,885
On the first day, there's already an embarrassment for you, Nalin.

299
00:28:43,438 --> 00:28:44,811
Not at all.

300
00:28:45,753 --> 00:28:48,846
It's almost lunch break, so I'll get straight to the point.

301
00:28:51,931 --> 00:28:53,582
Our school

302
00:28:53,583 --> 00:28:57,288
will send 11th-grade students to a French competition.

303
00:29:03,890 --> 00:29:07,454
Even though targeted therapy is expensive,

304
00:29:08,522 --> 00:29:12,632
I still want Teacher Niramon to have a chance to keep fighting.

305
00:29:15,356 --> 00:29:17,246
You know about this, Mother?

306
00:29:20,629 --> 00:29:22,436
You probably didn't know

307
00:29:22,803 --> 00:29:24,763
that teachers who take students to competitions

308
00:29:24,764 --> 00:29:27,194
and bring honor to the school

309
00:29:27,959 --> 00:29:30,434
will receive a bonus as a token of appreciation.

310
00:29:31,882 --> 00:29:34,459
Why are you being so kind to me, Mother?

311
00:29:37,063 --> 00:29:41,335
Because helping and standing by our teachers

312
00:29:41,695 --> 00:29:44,274
who are in difficult situations

313
00:29:45,577 --> 00:29:48,174
is quite normal for our school.

314
00:29:48,641 --> 00:29:50,498
I want you

315
00:29:51,025 --> 00:29:55,095
to accept this goodwill, don't overthink it.

316
00:29:55,979 --> 00:29:57,549
Besides,

317
00:29:57,550 --> 00:30:02,162
Teacher Niramon has been teaching at our school for decades.

318
00:30:03,270 --> 00:30:05,316
The love and care we have for her

319
00:30:05,676 --> 00:30:08,445
is no different from that of family.

320
00:30:14,496 --> 00:30:16,342
[Dad's truck broke down.]

321
00:30:16,342 --> 00:30:19,646
[We can't deliver to clients on time. It's a big mess, honey.]

322
00:30:19,646 --> 00:30:21,969
[If mom doesn't get paid by the clients...]

323
00:30:21,970 --> 00:30:24,825
[We might have to pay your tuition a little late.]

324
00:30:24,825 --> 00:30:27,651
[Will the school be okay with that?]

325
00:30:30,545 --> 00:30:31,712
You're Earn, right?

326
00:30:32,484 --> 00:30:33,704
Yes.

327
00:30:36,987 --> 00:30:38,556
I heard you're an excellent student.

328
00:30:40,406 --> 00:30:42,888
I want to invite you to join the French competition.

329
00:30:43,776 --> 00:30:46,474
But I just transferred to the French Arts track.

330
00:30:46,475 --> 00:30:49,932
You just joined the French Arts track this semester,

331
00:30:50,173 --> 00:30:52,074
and you already got a 4.0.

332
00:30:53,436 --> 00:30:55,062
That's not ordinary.

333
00:30:55,637 --> 00:30:57,237
You can definitely compete.

334
00:31:02,564 --> 00:31:08,141
Well, if it were a general knowledge or a quiz competition,

335
00:31:08,361 --> 00:31:10,121
I might give it a try.

336
00:31:10,122 --> 00:31:14,884
But for a speaking competition, I'm not really confident.

337
00:31:15,904 --> 00:31:17,724
These things require practice.

338
00:31:18,090 --> 00:31:19,801
With practice, we can definitely do it.

339
00:31:24,792 --> 00:31:26,169
And also,

340
00:31:28,915 --> 00:31:31,317
Mother Superior is very worried about you.

341
00:31:32,716 --> 00:31:34,881
She told me everything.

342
00:31:34,882 --> 00:31:36,994
About you losing your full scholarship.

343
00:31:40,436 --> 00:31:43,376
If you join the French competition and win...

344
00:31:44,304 --> 00:31:45,670
I think...

345
00:31:46,404 --> 00:31:49,234
the prize money should make it worth your while.

346
00:31:58,309 --> 00:31:59,830
Okay, Teacher.

347
00:32:02,199 --> 00:32:03,385
Great.

348
00:32:03,807 --> 00:32:07,135
Don't worry, I'll tutor you with everything I've got.

349
00:32:10,249 --> 00:32:11,763
But...

350
00:32:11,958 --> 00:32:14,271
Can you recommend any other smart students?

351
00:32:14,944 --> 00:32:17,691
For the French competition, we need 4 people.

352
00:32:17,692 --> 00:32:18,932
Yes, I can.

353
00:32:18,933 --> 00:32:22,706
This person is the best at French in the whole school.

354
00:32:26,320 --> 00:32:27,654
But...

355
00:32:27,654 --> 00:32:29,934
It might be a little hard to persuade her.

356
00:32:41,634 --> 00:32:43,142
Nicharee.

357
00:32:46,448 --> 00:32:47,784
Nicharee.

358
00:32:57,014 --> 00:32:58,488
I'm not interested.

359
00:33:07,227 --> 00:33:08,949
Why don't you at least give it a try?

360
00:33:09,315 --> 00:33:11,212
Your friends told me you're very good at it.

361
00:33:12,021 --> 00:33:13,301
I'm not a rooster.

362
00:33:13,754 --> 00:33:15,554
I don't like competing.

363
00:33:20,203 --> 00:33:22,184
But you'll be in 12th grade next year.

364
00:33:23,721 --> 00:33:26,712
Having a record of academic competitions

365
00:33:26,713 --> 00:33:29,869
will look great on your portfolio, making it easier to get into university.

366
00:33:30,620 --> 00:33:32,562
I don't want to go to university.

367
00:33:34,346 --> 00:33:35,823
There's prize money too.

368
00:33:36,682 --> 00:33:38,944
And I don't have any money problems.

369
00:33:39,805 --> 00:33:41,266
Or do you, Teacher?

370
00:33:43,893 --> 00:33:47,137
If you want the money so bad, why don't you compete yourself?

371
00:33:53,807 --> 00:33:55,520
Are you afraid of losing?

372
00:34:02,400 --> 00:34:03,493
Me?

373
00:34:06,356 --> 00:34:09,554
I don't like wasting time on things I don't see any benefit in.

374
00:34:13,456 --> 00:34:15,297
And honestly,

375
00:34:16,038 --> 00:34:17,852
you're wasting your time right now too.

376
00:34:21,314 --> 00:34:23,108
Excuse me, I'm going back to sleep.

377
00:35:25,721 --> 00:35:28,881
They say a love song

378
00:35:28,882 --> 00:35:30,882
can't be written without being in love.

379
00:35:30,883 --> 00:35:32,804
Hmm, does that mean

380
00:35:32,805 --> 00:35:35,621
P'Amy is in love?

381
00:35:38,355 --> 00:35:40,925
Well... I guess so.

382
00:35:44,317 --> 00:35:47,956
Oh, P'Sophie, our beautiful student council president is here too.

383
00:35:47,957 --> 00:35:50,099
Hello, P'Sophie.

384
00:35:51,518 --> 00:35:55,063
Alright everyone, we have a witness to help us find the answer

385
00:35:55,064 --> 00:35:57,737
to who exactly is P'Amy's sweetheart.

386
00:36:00,653 --> 00:36:02,086
I'm not telling just yet.

387
00:36:05,052 --> 00:36:07,738
Okay, okay, how about just the initials then?

388
00:36:15,496 --> 00:36:17,349
Initial...

389
00:36:18,033 --> 00:36:19,132
Well...

390
00:36:22,369 --> 00:36:23,589
Probably S.

391
00:36:26,026 --> 00:36:28,167
Is there anyone here whose name starts with S?

392
00:36:29,267 --> 00:36:32,484
Is it this person? Is this the S?

393
00:36:36,703 --> 00:36:39,287
Is it the S they're teasing about?

394
00:36:42,432 --> 00:36:46,567
I didn't even say which S. Don't tease her.

395
00:36:46,568 --> 00:36:50,066
But anyone around here named S would be dying of embarrassment.

396
00:36:55,421 --> 00:36:56,992
Who here has a name starting with S?

397
00:37:05,944 --> 00:37:07,404
Hello, Teacher Thip.

398
00:37:11,743 --> 00:37:14,976
Talking about romance and love is inappropriate.

399
00:37:16,253 --> 00:37:18,566
Sophie, you're the student council president.

400
00:37:18,567 --> 00:37:20,825
You should go and warn the broadcasting club.

401
00:37:21,247 --> 00:37:24,255
Tell them to organize more useful programs.

402
00:37:26,727 --> 00:37:28,127
And what is this?

403
00:37:29,111 --> 00:37:30,937
Why are girls screaming over other girls?

404
00:37:30,938 --> 00:37:34,110
This is a school, not some weirdos' association.

405
00:37:39,117 --> 00:37:40,599
You're right, Teacher Thip.

406
00:37:50,764 --> 00:37:51,786
Hey.

407
00:37:52,267 --> 00:37:53,299
What?

408
00:37:54,780 --> 00:37:56,320
Are you sure

409
00:37:56,321 --> 00:37:58,704
that you can rotate the sports day funds to pay me back first?

410
00:38:01,882 --> 00:38:03,822
Well, if you become the color president

411
00:38:03,823 --> 00:38:05,478
and I become the head cheerleader,

412
00:38:05,479 --> 00:38:07,819
the money will be with the two of us anyway, right?

413
00:38:08,521 --> 00:38:10,204
I'll handle it.

414
00:38:11,176 --> 00:38:13,664
That's why I'm asking if you're sure.

415
00:38:13,943 --> 00:38:16,243
I have to buy a fan meeting ticket this Friday.

416
00:38:16,498 --> 00:38:17,538
Ugh.

417
00:38:17,851 --> 00:38:19,311
Do you have to be so scared?

418
00:38:19,804 --> 00:38:21,608
I'll handle it for you.

419
00:38:21,609 --> 00:38:23,727
You'll definitely get to see your guys.

420
00:38:40,926 --> 00:38:43,359
What kind of person looks pretty from every angle?

421
00:39:00,649 --> 00:39:01,835
Jane.

422
00:39:03,613 --> 00:39:06,637
I only told you my name once, you remembered?

423
00:39:22,501 --> 00:39:24,432
Do you want to be friends with us?

424
00:39:29,064 --> 00:39:31,421
So, there will be a vote for color president soon.

425
00:39:31,422 --> 00:39:34,009
You just vote for Khaopan, and we'll let you join our group.

426
00:39:36,778 --> 00:39:38,498
Sure, I'm in.

427
00:39:41,417 --> 00:39:44,310
Everyone, the main theme for this year's sports day is

428
00:39:44,311 --> 00:39:45,660
"The Grand Journey".

429
00:39:45,661 --> 00:39:49,594
We'll have everyone brainstorm sub-themes, and then we'll vote.

430
00:39:49,595 --> 00:39:52,699
Whoever's theme wins will be the color president.

431
00:39:52,700 --> 00:39:55,464
Therefore, I want everyone to vote thoughtfully.

432
00:39:55,771 --> 00:39:57,451
What theme should we go with?

433
00:39:57,451 --> 00:39:59,001
Don't think too hard about it.

434
00:39:59,001 --> 00:40:01,687
Nano will just lock the votes for Khaopan anyway.

435
00:40:01,687 --> 00:40:03,373
There's no point suggesting anything.

436
00:40:08,524 --> 00:40:10,069
Time Travel sounds good.

437
00:40:23,106 --> 00:40:25,543
The first theme is Around The World.

438
00:40:25,751 --> 00:40:27,031
Who votes for this theme?

439
00:40:32,007 --> 00:40:33,327
Alright, next theme.

440
00:40:33,913 --> 00:40:36,700
"Fairy Tale," doing something with fairy tales.

441
00:40:36,701 --> 00:40:39,053
This one is Khaopan's. Who votes for it?

442
00:40:53,231 --> 00:40:54,671
The last theme.

443
00:40:55,021 --> 00:40:56,905
"Time Travel"

444
00:40:56,906 --> 00:41:00,378
anyone can wear whatever crazy things they want.

445
00:41:04,032 --> 00:41:05,589
We can wear whatever crazy things?

446
00:41:05,590 --> 00:41:07,036
Like a dinosaur with dolly eyes?

447
00:41:08,286 --> 00:41:10,004
A dinosaur with dolly eyes,

448
00:41:10,005 --> 00:41:11,851
but wearing a Thai traditional dance costume.

449
00:41:14,782 --> 00:41:18,122
Okay, okay, stop. So who votes for this theme?

450
00:41:24,501 --> 00:41:26,068
Let me ask...

451
00:41:26,394 --> 00:41:28,373
Who came up with this theme?

452
00:41:39,761 --> 00:41:41,867
Way to go, new kid.

453
00:42:14,585 --> 00:42:17,478
Sorry, our class just finished choosing a theme.

454
00:42:18,217 --> 00:42:19,425
Let's start discussing.

455
00:42:21,983 --> 00:42:25,018
We saw what theme the French class chose.

456
00:42:26,135 --> 00:42:28,048
It seems we picked the same theme.

457
00:42:28,607 --> 00:42:29,694
What should we do?

458
00:42:33,268 --> 00:42:35,275
Then your class can take this theme.

459
00:42:35,275 --> 00:42:36,995
We'll go pick a new one.

460
00:42:37,905 --> 00:42:39,345
Hey, wait a minute.

461
00:42:39,982 --> 00:42:40,988
Well...

462
00:42:42,265 --> 00:42:44,752
I just feel bad for my classmates.

463
00:42:46,194 --> 00:42:49,131
Everyone contributed so many ideas just now.

464
00:42:52,241 --> 00:42:54,090
How about we compete with our ideas?

465
00:42:54,091 --> 00:42:58,071
Like, what kind of concept do you have in mind?

466
00:42:59,377 --> 00:43:02,340
So we can, you know, brainstorm together?

467
00:43:02,837 --> 00:43:05,051
Wow, that's hard.

468
00:43:05,411 --> 00:43:07,168
We just came up with the theme.

469
00:43:08,263 --> 00:43:10,433
But with Time Travel, you can do anything, right?

470
00:43:11,220 --> 00:43:13,448
Fairy Tale suits the French class well, though.

471
00:43:14,917 --> 00:43:15,923
Wait.

472
00:43:16,812 --> 00:43:19,887
How did you know our class had a Fairy Tale theme?

473
00:43:21,285 --> 00:43:23,732
Well... I asked around.

474
00:44:15,759 --> 00:44:18,887
If I had to come up with something quick...

475
00:44:19,067 --> 00:44:20,768
It would probably look something like this.

476
00:44:24,788 --> 00:44:26,418
A time machine.

477
00:44:26,639 --> 00:44:30,735
And then we have mascots that can keep changing.

478
00:44:31,551 --> 00:44:35,671
Like... a dinosaur, an ancient Chinese series character...

479
00:44:35,672 --> 00:44:37,408
Or whoever anyone wants.

480
00:44:37,409 --> 00:44:39,809
But all those things, my classmates helped suggest them.

481
00:44:39,810 --> 00:44:41,694
I didn't think of it all myself.

482
00:44:41,695 --> 00:44:43,264
What do you think?

483
00:44:45,005 --> 00:44:46,065
Wow.

484
00:44:46,955 --> 00:44:49,075
If the picture is this clear...

485
00:44:49,403 --> 00:44:51,406
Then our class will just choose another theme.

486
00:44:52,936 --> 00:44:55,520
At first, I thought Khaopan was the color president.

487
00:44:57,387 --> 00:45:00,049
I didn't think the new student in Class C would be this talented.

488
00:45:01,205 --> 00:45:03,987
It should definitely make the French class look a lot more interesting.

489
00:45:04,921 --> 00:45:06,468
Compared to the past.

490
00:45:18,499 --> 00:45:19,811
Alright, everyone.

491
00:45:19,812 --> 00:45:22,722
Please the color president representatives come to discuss the details.

492
00:45:23,854 --> 00:45:25,080
Come over here.

493
00:46:05,613 --> 00:46:07,545
Where do we normally go after school?

494
00:46:12,033 --> 00:46:13,446
Hey, wait.

495
00:46:16,270 --> 00:46:18,927
Why do you even want to be friends with us?

496
00:46:21,343 --> 00:46:23,350
I know you're naive,

497
00:46:24,331 --> 00:46:26,688
but I didn't think you'd be this clueless.

498
00:46:35,125 --> 00:46:36,629
Hey, Jane.

499
00:46:36,630 --> 00:46:38,665
Does it snow in Chiang Rai now?

500
00:46:39,558 --> 00:46:40,790
It's all over your skirt.

501
00:47:49,202 --> 00:47:52,654
May I walk with you, Madam President?

502
00:47:55,154 --> 00:47:58,358
Today you intentionally hinted at my name for the whole school to hear.

503
00:48:00,182 --> 00:48:01,701
Wow, babe.

504
00:48:01,702 --> 00:48:04,005
I'm talking to a lot of people whose names start with S.

505
00:48:04,603 --> 00:48:06,129
No one could guess it right.

506
00:48:07,912 --> 00:48:08,919
Really?

507
00:48:09,387 --> 00:48:11,061
Thanks for letting me know.

508
00:48:13,403 --> 00:48:14,965
Yeah, but I saw it.

509
00:48:14,966 --> 00:48:17,879
You just walked away when friends were teasing Baipor.

510
00:48:18,505 --> 00:48:19,565
Are you jealous?

511
00:48:21,227 --> 00:48:23,326
I don't get jealous, we're not even a thing.

512
00:48:24,310 --> 00:48:25,365
Okay.

513
00:48:25,564 --> 00:48:27,634
Not jealous, then not jealous.

514
00:48:31,920 --> 00:48:35,047
See you at home later. About that homework...

515
00:48:35,048 --> 00:48:37,787
If you get it wrong, you'll definitely be punished.

516
00:48:41,423 --> 00:48:43,423
I'm going to get every question wrong.

517
00:48:44,827 --> 00:48:46,548
I want to be punished already.

518
00:49:51,532 --> 00:49:52,913
That was pretty exhausting.

519
00:50:31,875 --> 00:50:33,915
Pan, what are you doing?
